                <h2 style="color:white;"><b>Introduction - What is Path Traversal?</b></h2><br>
                <p> Directory traversal (also known as file path traversal) is a web security vulnerability that allows an attacker to read arbitrary files on the server that is running an application.
                    <br>
                    This might include application code and data, credentials for back-end systems, also sensitive files such as <b>/etc/passwd</b> or <b>/etc/shadow</b> on the server running the Web Application.
                    <br><br>
					<b>Note that</b>: This vulnerability only appears in <b>filebase</b> Programming Language such as PHP.., the <b>routebase</b> Programming Language such as NodeJS, ASP, Golang.. are not affected by this vulnerability.
					<br>
					
